[~sjones]:  OK, so I created this custom IAM policy for a user in order to allow adding Access Keys to their own account:
{code}
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17", 
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Action": "iam:CreateAccessKey", 
      "Resource": "*", 
      "Effect": "Allow"
    }, 
    {
      "Action": "iam:DeleteAccessKey", 
      "Resource": "*", 
      "Effect": "Allow"
    }, 
    {
      "Action": "iam:ListAccessKeys", 
      "Resource": "*", 
      "Effect": "Allow"
    }, 
    {
      "Action": "iam:UpdateAccessKey", 
      "Resource": "*", 
      "Effect": "Allow"
    }
  ]
}
{code}

Based on this policy, along with PowerUser access, should this user be able to add an AccessKey?  Because currently, they cannot.
